The paper presents a method for image quality assessment, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The method involves extracting features from the image using entropy, which is a common technique in information theory (cs.IT). The use of support vector machines for classification and regression is also common in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper evaluates the proposed method on two image databases, which involves statistical analysis and performance evaluation, which could fall under the category of multimedia (cs.MM).
